            "en": "<p>To be recognised as an inspection body, you must fulfil:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all recognitions relating to the environment<ul><li>in the 3 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a>, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>special recognition conditions</strong>:<ul><li>hold accreditation as type A inspectorate according to the <strong>ISO 17020</strong> for the inspection of refrigeration companies</li><li>or be accredited as an inspection body according to the <strong>ISO 17020</strong> standard and supply proof that an application for accreditation for the inspection of refrigeration companies has been accepted by the <strong>Belgian accreditation organisation BELAC</strong> or an equivalent accreditation system.</li></ul></li></ul><h2><strong>Validity period and obligations</strong></h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. The inspection body must meet the following obligations to retain the validity of the recognition:</p><ul><li>The inspectors must be recognised as refrigeration technician category 1 or have at least 3 years’ practical experience in the refrigeration sector.</li><li>The inspection must be performed on the basis of a checklist.</li><li>A summary of the companies that were recognised must be submitted to the Flemish adminigstration each month.</li></ul>",
